Rating: 1
I hate to cast aspersions, but this recipe is just so-so. If you want a simpler, better recipe, put a little butter in the saucepan, pour in 1/4 cup of white wine, then 1/2 cup of arborio rice and 2 cups chicken stock in small intervals. Take the rice off the burner and pour in 1/2 a can of black beans(the ones already in spices taste best as opposed to the plain beans). Finally, put in about 1/2 cup of colby jack cheese and prepare yourself for the eternal adoration of your table. I make this for non-risotto lovers who now request this dish. You can also substitute other things for the beans- like mushrooms or shellfish. So much easier and tastier than this interpretation.

